story.title: PROposal - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: PROposal: Hi! Welcome to PROposal! The app that helps you craft your perfect proposal!
story.creator: web-uploader

messages.text: Hi! Welcome to PROposal! The app that helps you craft your perfect proposal!
That’s what I need. How do we start?
First, enter in information regarding your soon-to-be fiancé!
OK. Her name is Sarah.
And what does Sarah like?
Well, she loves music and concerts.
Noted. What else?
Walking on the beach and having oceanside bon fires.
Good! We just need one more piece of information regarding your fiancé.
She loves to laugh. She’s always joking around and smiling.
Wonderful! Computing proposal portals. Please wait…
Complete!
OK, now what?
You will soon experience a simulated scenario where you can propose to Sarah…
And see if the setting will be right for the two of you.
Sounds good.
Please put on your VR glasses.
OK, on.
When you are ready to begin, please say, “Enter proposal” to begin your first proposal simulation.
OK…Enter proposal.
Initiating the perfect proposal!
What do you think?
Whoa. This is awesome.
Please provide feedback regarding which pieces of the proposal scenario are desired and undesired.
Well the concert is great! How did you know her favorite band?
I performed a quick social media search.
She looks like she is enjoying herself…
The lights just dimmed and they started playing her favorite song…
The main singer is calling us onstage…Whoa, this is weird…
Now we’re in front of everyone!
She looks kind of nervous…
She doesn’t really love being the center of attention…
Might want to get on one knee.
Why?
Oh WOW. The crowd just spelled out “Marry Me” with their phones?!
Why is she super pale?
OMG! SHE JUST THREW UP AND RAN AWAY!
She left me alone on stage! WTF?!
Is this an undesired proposal scenario?
What? YES!
Very undesired!
Ending proposal simulation.
What was that?! That is not what I call the perfect proposal.
Thank you for your feedback. Re-computing based upon simulation results.
Wait, that was your suggestion?
That’s how you want me to propose?
PROposal utilizes results of many simulations to create the perfect proposal.
We thank you for your patience in the process.
Fine…so now what?
When you are ready, please send message saying “Enter proposal” to begin your second proposal simulation.
This better be good…Enter proposal.
Initiating the perfect proposal!
OK…so far this is much more simple. That’s good.
Good touch on the coffee shop…let me guess, social media search?
You got it. Besides her home, she spends the most time at coffee shops.
Looks like we’re at another performance, huh?
I think this one is better though. She likes smaller venues.
Plus, that’s one of her favorite comedians up there. She’s cracking up!
OK he just told everyone to reach under their chairs…
She found a small box underneath hers…
She’s opening it…Wait, what the heck?!
What’s wrong?
She just got squirted in the face from something in the box!
And why did the note have to be so lame?
“You make my heart burst! I want to laugh with you forever. Marry me?”
What do you think?
It was terrible. She was PISSED.
She just told me that I never take anything seriously and walked away.
Is this an undesired component of proposal?
YES!
Ending proposal stimulation.
OK, I’m about to give up. Maybe I shouldn’t propose after all…
It seems like she’s just going to say no to me, no matter what I do.
Please be patient as we re-compute based upon simulation results.
Simulation three ready to be initiated.
Please send message saying “Enter proposal” to begin your third proposal simulation.
Fine…but after this, I’m done…Enter proposal.
What do you think?
It’s beautiful…
WAIT! This is where we went on our first date…
Yes. I searched your pictures and matched it on maps to locate the correct beach.
It’s peaceful here. We’re walking along the shore…
OK, nice. There’s a bonfire in the distance…
She’s laughing because the breeze keeps causing my hair to be all messed up.
She always thinks that’s funny for some reason…
So far so good?
Yeah…so far so good. Do I hear music?
Wow. Nice touch having Bobby play the guitar. He’s one of our good friends.
And he’s playing her favorite song…I think you may have nailed it.
Now she’s freaking out because she saw the s’mores supplies. She LOVES s’mores!
Hold on, there’s something in my pocket…
It’s the ring. How’d that get there?
That’s part of the simulation.
You’re not going to do the actual proposal part this time?!
Per our computations, your perfect proposal requires you to complete this portion on your own.
Well great…this is the most nerve-racking part.
Dalton turns to the hologram of Sarah.
In his VR glasses she looks so real…
That it isn’t hard to imagine that she’s right there before him.
And her presence instantly calms him.
He opens his mouth and pours out his soul.
Sarah, I love you and I want to spend the rest of my life with you.
I want to always make you laugh, and be there for you when you cry…
And take you to big events, and celebrate life’s important moments with you.
But most of all, I want to be with you for the quiet times too…
The walks along the beach. The smiles shared between us.
So Sarah…
Dalton gets down on one knee.
Will you marry me?
A few minutes later, Dalton feels his phone vibrate.
How’d it go?
SHE SAID YES!!!
And now our best friends are here to join us!
I swear, I’ve never seen her look so happy…
She said the proposal was better than anything she’s ever imagined.
Great! Ending proposal simulation.
Wait! I don’t want it to end!
I’m sorry, simulation has been completed. Please provide feedback.
I cannot believe how amazing that was.
Wonderful! So, has the perfect proposal been created?
Yes! THANK YOU!
Our pleasure! You are now a proposal PRO. Please tell your friends about our app and like us on social media.
I definitely will! After the proposal, of course…
Because now I just have to buy a ring…
